  <article class="pa3 ph5-ns">
    <h3 class="f6 ttu tracked mt0">Heights</h3>
    <p class="measure f3 lh-copy">
      The heights module contains both a five-step height scale based on powers
      of two as well as a series of percentage values. Explicit values can be
      used inside of any parent. Percentage values will only work inside of a
      parent element that has a declared height.
    </p>
    <p class="measure f4 lh-copy">
      Class name structure is as follows:
    </p>
    <pre>Base: h = height Modifiers 1 = 1st step in height scale 2 = 2nd step in
      height scale 3 = 3rd step in height scale 4 = 4th step in height scale 5 =
      5th step in height scale -25 -50 -75 -100 -auto = string value auto Media
      Query Extensions: -ns = not-small -m = medium -l = large
    </pre>
  </article>
